column11:
  In this paper we introduce the notion of universe, induced communities and
cells with their corresponding spots. Using this language we formulate and
prove the union close set conjecture by showing that for any finite universe
$\mathbb{U}$ and any induced community $\mathcal{M}_{\mathbb{U}}$ there exist
some spot $a\in \mathbb{U}$ such that the density \begin{align}
\mathcal{D}_{\mathcal{M}_{\mathbb{U}}}(a)\geq \frac{1}{2}.\nonumber \end{align}
